HEADWORD: Botocudos
<hw>Bo`to*cu"dos</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[Pg.
<ets>botoque</ets> stopple. So called because they wear a wooden plug in
the pierced lower lip.]</ety> <def>A Brazilian tribe of Indians, noted
for their use of poisons; -- also called
<xex>Aymbor⟦eacute⟧s</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

